Prompt Dependencies:
- types_TypeScript.prompt — provides `Job`, `JobStatus`
- lib_jobs_TypeScript.prompt — provides `getJob`, `retryJob`

Instructions
- Use Next.js App Router dynamic route: `export async function POST(request: Request, { params }: { params: { id: string } })`.
- First call `getJob(params.id)` to validate existence and status before retrying.
- If job not found: return 404.
- If job status is not `'error'`: return 400.
- Call `retryJob(params.id)`. Return `{ jobId: params.id }`.
- Return 500 with error message if `retryJob` throws.

Deliverable
- `app/api/jobs/[id]/retry/route.ts` — POST handler for retrying failed jobs.

Implementation assumptions (explicit)
- `retryJob` is an async function in `lib/jobs.ts` that resets status and re-executes the same pipeline stage.
- The retry is non-blocking by default; the client subscribes to the SSE stream at `/api/jobs/{id}/stream` for progress.

Please produce production-ready TypeScript code consistent with the above.
